{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885857779,"sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0ba335001iASrwkuE04NnQI","messageID":"msg_d7b0b9553001hZagu14d23in9W","sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_71746b35ad3341a08a2e17eb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** integrations  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Plugin Bootstrap and Entry Point\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T1.1** Create main.py entry point\n13:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n14:   - Import: `Plugin`, `DifyPluginEnv` from `dify_plugin`\n15:   - Code: `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n16:   - Verify: File exists with correct entry point\n17: \n18: - [ ] **T1.2** Create requirements.txt with pinned dependencies\n19:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n20:   - Add: `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n21:   - Add: `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n22:   - Verify: Both dependencies listed with correct version bounds\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.3** Create .difyignore for packaging\n25:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore`\n26:   - Add common ignore patterns (e.g., `__pycache__`, `*.pyc`, `.git`)\n27:   - Verify: File exists with ignore patterns\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Phase 2: Plugin Manifest (manifest.yaml)\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T2.1** Define manifest top-level metadata\n34:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n35:   - Add: `version: 0.0.2`\n36:   - Add: `type: plugin`\n37:   - Add: `author: volcano-sh`\n38:   - Add: `name: agentcube`\n39:   - Verify: All fields present\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.2** Add multilingual labels and descriptions\n42:   - Add: `label` with keys `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n43:   - Add: `description` with multilingual strings for each locale\n44:   - Verify: All 4 locales present in both label and description\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.3** Configure icon resources\n47:   - Add: `icon: icon.png`\n48:   - Add: `icon_dark: icon-dark.png`\n49:   - Verify: Both icon fields reference correct files\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.4** Define resource requirements and permissions\n52:   - Add: `resource` block with:\n53:     - `memory` specification\n54:     - `permission` subtree with flags: `tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage`\n55:   - Verify: Resource block complete with all permission flags\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.5** Register tool provider in manifest\n58:   - Add: `plugins.tools: [provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n59:   - Verify: Tool provider path listed\n60: \n61: - [ ] **T2.6** Add meta section with runtime metadata\n62:   - Add: `meta.version` matching plugin version\n63:   - Add: `meta.arch: [amd64, arm64]`\n64:   - Add: `meta.runner` with `language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`\n65:   - Add: `meta.minimum_dify_version: null`\n66:   - Verify: All meta fields present\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T2.7** Add optional metadata fields\n69:   - Add: `created_at` timestamp\n70:   - Add: `privacy` reference\n71:   - Add: `repo` URL\n72:   - Add: `verified` flag\n73:   - Verify: Optional fields present\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Phase 3: Tool Provider Descriptor (provider/agentcube.yaml)\n78: \n79: - [ ] **T3.1** Create provider directory structure\n80:   - Directory: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/`\n81:   - Verify: Directory exists\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.2** Define provider identity\n84:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n85:   - Add: `identity.author: agentcube`\n86:   - Add: `identity.name: agentcube`\n87:   - Add: `identity.label` with multilingual strings\n88:   - Add: `identity.description` with multilingual strings\n89:   - Add: `identity.icon: icon.png`\n90:   - Verify: All identity fields present\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T3.3** List associated tools\n93:   - Add: `tools: [tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n94:   - Verify: Tool path listed\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T3.4** Configure Python source entry\n97:   - Add: `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n98:   - Verify: Source path points to provider implementation\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 4: Tool Parameter Schema (tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml)\n103: \n104: - [ ] **T4.1** Create tools directory structure\n105:   - Directory: `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/`\n106:   - Verify: Directory exists\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T4.2** Define tool identity\n109:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n110:   - Add: `identity.name: agentcube-code-interpreter`\n111:   - Add: `identity.author: agentcube`\n112:   - Add: `identity.label` with multilingual strings (human + llm)\n113:   - Add: `identity.description` with multilingual strings (human + llm)\n114:   - Verify: All identity fields present\n115: \n116: - [ ] **T4.3** Define router_url parameter\n117:   - Add parameter block for `router_url`:\n118:     - `type: string`\n119:     - `required: true`\n120:     - `form: form`\n121:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n122:   - Verify: Parameter complete\n123: \n124: - [ ] **T4.4** Define workload_manager_url parameter\n125:   - Add parameter block for `workload_manager_url`:\n126:     - `type: string`\n127:     - `required: true`\n128:     - `form: form`\n129:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n130:   - Verify: Parameter complete\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T4.5** Define language parameter (optional select)\n133:   - Add parameter block for `language`:\n134:     - `type: select`\n135:     - `required: false`\n136:     - `form: llm`\n137:     - `options: [python, javascript, typescript]`\n138:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n139:   - Verify: Parameter with options complete\n140: \n141: - [ ] **T4.6** Define code parameter (optional)\n142:   - Add parameter block for `code`:\n143:     - `type: string`\n144:     - `required: false`\n145:     - `form: llm`\n146:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n147:   - Verify: Parameter complete\n148: \n149: - [ ] **T4.7** Define command parameter (optional)\n150:   - Add parameter block for `command`:\n151:     - `type: string`\n152:     - `required: false`\n153:     - `form: llm`\n154:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n155:   - Verify: Parameter complete\n156: \n157: - [ ] **T4.8** Define session_id parameter (optional)\n158:   - Add parameter block for `session_id`:\n159:     - `type: string`\n160:     - `required: false`\n161:     - `form: llm`\n162:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n163:   - Verify: Parameter complete\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T4.9** Define session_reuse parameter (optional boolean)\n166:   - Add parameter block for `session_reuse`:\n167:     - `type: boolean`\n168:     - `required: false`\n169:     - `form: llm`\n170:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n171:   - Verify: Parameter complete\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T4.10** Define code_interpreter_id parameter (optional)\n174:   - Add parameter block for `code_interpreter_id`:\n175:     - `type: string`\n176:     - `required: false`\n177:     - `form: llm`\n178:     - `label` and `human_description` and `llm_description`\n179:   - Verify: Parameter complete\n180: \n181: - [ ] **T4.11** Configure Python source entry\n182:   - Add: `extra.python.source: tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n183:   - Verify: Source path points to tool implementation\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## Phase 5: Provider Implementation (provider/agentcube.py)\n188: \n189: - [ ] **T5.1** Create provider Python module\n190:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n191:   - Import: `ToolProvider` from `dify_plugin`\n192:   - Import: `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` from `dify_plugin.errors.tool`\n193:   - Import: `Any` from `typing`\n194:   - Verify: Imports present\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T5.2** Define AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider class\n197:   - Class: `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider)`\n198:   - Verify: Class inherits from ToolProvider\n199: \n200: - [ ] **T5.3** Implement _validate_credentials method\n201:   - Method: `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None`\n202:   - Wrap validation logic in try-except block\n203:   - On exception: raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))`\n204:   - Verify: Method signature and error handling correct\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ## Phase 6: Tool Implementation (tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py)\n209: \n210: - [ ] **T6.1** Create tool Python module\n211:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n212:   - Import: `Generator` from `collections.abc`\n213:   - Import: `Any` from `typing`\n214:   - Import: `Tool` from `dify_plugin`\n215:   - Import: `ToolInvokeMessage` from `dify_plugin.entities.tool`\n216:   - Import: `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube`\n217:   - Verify: All imports present\n218: \n219: - [ ] **T6.2** Define AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool class\n220:   - Class: `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool)`\n221:   - Verify: Class inherits from Tool\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T6.3** Implement _invoke method\n224:   - Method: `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]`\n225:   - Call: `self.execute(**tool_parameters)`\n226:   - Yield: `self.create_json_message(result)`\n227:   - Verify: Method signature and yield pattern correct\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T6.4** Implement execute method signature\n230:   - Method: `execute(self, router_url=None, workload_manager_url=None, language=\"python\", code_interpreter_id=None, session_id=None, code=None, command=None, session_reuse=False, **kwargs)`\n231:   - Verify: All parameters match tool schema\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T6.5** Implement execute method body\n234:   - Use `CodeInterpreterClient` with `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n235:   - Handle optional `language` parameter (default `python`)\n236:   - Handle optional `code` and/or `command` execution\n237:   - Handle optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, `code_interpreter_id`\n238:   - Return: JSON-serializable result object\n239:   - Verify: All parameters handled and result returned\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## Phase 7: Documentation Files\n244: \n245: - [ ] **T7.1** Create README.md\n246:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md`\n247:   - Include: Plugin overview, installation instructions, usage examples\n248:   - Verify: File exists with content\n249: \n250: - [ ] **T7.2** Create GUIDE.md\n251:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md`\n252:   - Include: Detailed integration guide for Dify platform\n253:   - Verify: File exists with content\n254: \n255: - [ ] **T7.3** Create PRIVACY.md\n256:   - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md`\n257:   - Include: Privacy policy and data handling information\n258:   - Verify: File exists with content\n259: \n260: - [ ] **T7.4** Add icon files\n261:   - Files: `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png`, `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png`\n262:   - Verify: Both icon files exist\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ## Phase 8: Verification and Testing\n267: \n268: - [ ] **T8.1** Verify manifest structure\n269:   - Command: Parse `manifest.yaml` with YAML parser\n270:   - Check: All required fields present (`version`, `type`, `author`, `name`, `label`, `description`, `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource`, `plugins.tools`, `meta`)\n271:   - Verify: Manifest validates successfully\n272: \n273: - [ ] **T8.2** Verify provider descriptor structure\n274:   - Check: `provider/agentcube.yaml` has `identity`, `tools`, `extra.python.source`\n275:   - Verify: Provider descriptor complete\n276: \n277: - [ ] **T8.3** Verify tool schema structure\n278:   - Check: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` has all 8 parameters defined\n279:   - Check: Required parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`) marked as required\n280:   - Check: Optional parameters marked correctly\n281:   - Verify: Tool schema complete\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T8.4** Verify Python module imports\n284:   - Command: `python -c \"import provider.agentcube\"` (with dependencies installed)\n285:   - Command: `python -c \"import tools.agentcube_code_interpreter\"` (with dependencies installed)\n286:   - Verify: Modules import without errors\n287: \n288: - [ ] **T8.5** Verify requirements.txt dependencies\n289:   - Command: `pip install -r requirements.txt` (dry-run or in venv)\n290:   - Verify: Dependencies install successfully\n291: \n292: - [ ] **T8.6** Verify file structure matches design.md\n293:   - Check: All 9 files from design.md file map present:\n294:     - `main.py`, `manifest.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.yaml`, `provider/agentcube.py`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`, `requirements.txt`, `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore`\n295:   - Verify: Complete file structure\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Acceptance Criteria\n300: \n301: 1. ✅ `main.py` runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n302: 2. ✅ `manifest.yaml` contains all required top-level keys and structure\n303: 3. ✅ Multilingual labels and descriptions present for 4 locales (en_US, ja_JP, zh_Hans, pt_BR)\n304: 4. ✅ Resource permissions include tool, model, endpoint, app, storage flags\n305: 5. ✅ Tool provider registered in `plugins.tools` list\n306: 6. ✅ Meta section specifies Python 3.12 runner with main entrypoint\n307: 7. ✅ `provider/agentcube.yaml` defines identity, tools list, and Python source\n308: 8. ✅ Tool schema declares all 8 parameters with correct types and forms\n309: 9. ✅ Required parameters (`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`) marked as required=true\n310: 10. ✅ Language parameter offers select options: python, javascript, typescript\n311: 11. ✅ Provider class implements `_validate_credentials` with error handling\n312: 12. ✅ Tool class implements `_invoke` yielding JSON message\n313: 13. ✅ Tool class implements `execute` with all parameters matching schema\n314: 14. ✅ Requirements.txt pins `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n315: 15. ✅ Documentation files present: README.md, GUIDE.md, PRIVACY.md\n316: 16. ✅ Icon files present: icon.png, icon-dark.png\n317: 17. ✅ .difyignore present with common ignore patterns\n318: 18. ✅ File structure matches design.md (11 files total)\n319: 19. ✅ All YAML files parse without syntax errors\n320: 20. ✅ Python modules import successfully with dependencies installed\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: **Notes:**\n325: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (Dify plugin structure created)\n326: - Uses dify-plugin framework v0.4.x with agentcube-sdk v0.0.10+\n327: - Python runtime: 3.12 (specified in manifest.meta.runner)\n328: - Supports amd64 and arm64 architectures\n329: - Tool provider delegates to AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient\n330: - Plugin integrates with Dify's tool invocation framework\n331: - Credential validation raises ToolProviderCredentialValidationError on failure\n332: - Tool execution returns JSON-serializable results via create_json_message\n333: - File structure follows Dify plugin conventions from reference implementation\n334: \n335: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 335 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Plugin Bootstrap and Entry Point\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create main.py entry point\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n  - Import: `Plugin`, `DifyPluginEnv` from `dify_plugin`\n  - Code: `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n  - Verify: File exists with correct entry point\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create requirements.txt with pinned dependencies\n  - File: `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n  - Add: `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775885857727,"end":1775885857777}}}}
