{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885866705,"sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0bd1f5001wJKQoleBubwPsA","messageID":"msg_d7b0bb426001O48Z8LC5Je6oQC","sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ea2680cc66bf46a896e77948","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Integrations Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Normative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n10: \n11: The system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n16: - **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n17: - **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Plugin manifest structure\n22: \n23: The system SHALL ship a root `manifest.yaml` declaring plugin metadata, tool provider registration, resource permissions, and runner metadata sufficient for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Required manifest fields\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** a valid plugin package root\n28: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n29: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version`, `type: plugin`, `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual), `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource` (including `memory` and `permission` subtree), `plugins.tools` listing provider descriptors, and `meta` containing `version`, `arch`, `runner` (`language`, `version`, `entrypoint`), and `minimum_dify_version`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Tool provider wiring\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references the Agentcube provider descriptor\n34: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded\n35: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: Provider descriptor structure\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python provider implementation.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Provider lists tools and entry module\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is present\n46: - **WHEN** the integration runtime resolves the provider\n47: - **THEN** the descriptor SHALL include `identity` (author, name, multilingual label/description, icon), a `tools` list including `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: Tool parameter schema\n52: \n53: The system SHALL declare a tool schema for the code interpreter integration including connection endpoints, optional language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Declared parameters match remote APIs\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n58: - **WHEN** an operator configures the tool in Dify\n59: - **THEN** the schema SHALL require string parameters `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`, SHALL offer optional `language` as a select among `python`, `javascript`, and `typescript`, and SHALL allow optional `code`, `command`, `session_id`, `session_reuse` (boolean), and `code_interpreter_id`, each documented for human and LLM-oriented forms\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Tool provider credential validation\n64: \n65: The system SHALL implement credential validation on the tool provider class and SHALL surface validation failures using the Dify tool provider error type.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invalid credentials are rejected\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** an instance of `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`\n70: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition the implementer treats as invalid\n71: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Successful validation completes quietly\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** credentials that satisfy the provider’s validation rules\n76: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n77: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: Tool invocation and JSON messaging\n82: \n83: The system SHALL implement the Agentcube code interpreter tool as a Dify `Tool` that delegates execution and returns structured JSON to the host.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Dify invokes the tool\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** a configured tool invocation with parameters matching the schema\n88: - **WHEN** Dify calls `_invoke` on `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`\n89: - **THEN** the tool SHALL call `execute(**tool_parameters)` and SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Tool execution API surface\n94: \n95: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters for router and workload manager URLs, optional language, session controls, and code or command execution, delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Code or command runs against configured endpoints\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n100: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n101: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK client to perform the corresponding remote operations and SHALL return a JSON-serializable result object suitable for `create_json_message`\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Plugin Python dependencies\n106: \n107: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` for reproducible installs.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Dependency bounds\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n112: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n113: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer FastAPI service\n118: \n119: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup, composes LangChain/LangGraph agents, and exposes an analysis endpoint for PCAP uploads.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Startup requires API key\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the process is started without a usable `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent configured API key)\n124: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n125: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail rather than serve requests without credentials\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts PCAP input\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n130: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with either an uploaded PCAP file or a `pcap_path` form field\n131: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a body matching `AnalyzeResponse` including `script`, `results`, and `report`\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer configuration surface\n136: \n137: The system SHALL read runtime configuration from environment variables for the OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Defaults and overrides\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** standard deployment environment variables\n142: - **WHEN** the service starts\n143: - **THEN** it SHALL use `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` defaulting to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` defaulting to `default`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` defaulting to `5`, while binding HTTP to `0.0.0.0:8000` as defined in the application\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer sandbox integration\n148: \n149: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis by planning and repairing scripts, executing them inside an AgentCube-backed sandbox via `SandboxRunner`, and aggregating results through reporter agents.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Sandbox runner executes commands\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` constructed with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration\n154: - **WHEN** analysis logic invokes `run` with a shell command\n155: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and SHALL return structured execution results for downstream LLM steps\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: File staging uses runner uploads\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n160: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n161: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer container image\n166: \n167: The system SHALL build a container image that installs Python dependencies with `uv`, vendors the in-repo `agentcube` SDK copy, sets `PYTHONPATH`, exposes port 8000, and starts the FastAPI app via `uv run`.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Image entrypoint\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** the `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n172: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n173: - **THEN** the default command SHALL be `uv run pcap_analyzer.py` with `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` and port `8000` exposed\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n178: \n179: The system SHALL supply a `Deployment` manifest that runs the analyzer image with resource requests/limits and environment variables wired from a Secret and plain env for AgentCube and model endpoints.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Deployment wiring\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` applied to the cluster\n184: - **WHEN** the workload becomes ready\n185: - **THEN** the pod SHALL run image `pcap-analyzer:latest` (pull `IfNotPresent`), listen on TCP 8000, request `cpu: 200m` / `memory: 100Mi` and limit `cpu: 1` / `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, and set `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` as container environment variables\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Process launch in cluster\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** the deployment’s container specification\n190: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n191: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `uv` with arguments `run pcap_analyzer.py`, matching local Docker behavior\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Integrations Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nNormative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n\n- **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n- **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n- **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/spec.md","time":{"start":1775885866693,"end":1775885866703}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885866708,"sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0bc734001f13GILOEoJEdWw","messageID":"msg_d7b0bb426001O48Z8LC5Je6oQC","sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3a1debd41c8e479a9d447bd6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"AgentCube Python SDK.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n4: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n5: \n6: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"AgentCube Python SDK.\"\"\"\n\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py","time":{"start":1775885866687,"end":1775885866707}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885866711,"sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0bcc8c001AbWy6CdbpY1u0Z","messageID":"msg_d7b0bb426001O48Z8LC5Je6oQC","sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_669c7af4e1184fde9e6bbcda","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Code Interpreter Client for the agentcube SDK.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import logging\n4: import os\n5: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n6: \n7: from .clients.code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n8: from .clients.control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\n9: from .exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n10: from .utils.log import get_logger\n11: \n12: \n13: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n14:     \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter operations.\n15:     \n16:     This client manages session lifecycle and provides a simplified\n17:     interface for code execution and file operations.\n18:     \n19:     Attributes:\n20:         namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n21:         router_url: Router base URL\n22:         workload_manager_url: Workload Manager base URL\n23:         verbose: Enable debug logging flag\n24:         session_id: Session identifier\n25:         timeout: Default request timeout in seconds\n26:         connect_timeout: Connection timeout in seconds\n27:         cp_client: Control plane client instance\n28:         dp_client: Data plane client instance\n29:         logger: Module logger\n30:     \n31:     Example usage:\n32:         # Context manager pattern (recommended)\n33:         with CodeInterpreterClient(\n34:             namespace=\"default\",\n35:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n36:             workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n37:         ) as client:\n38:             result = client.execute(\"print('hello')\")\n39:             print(result)\n40:             client.upload_file(\"data.txt\", b\"sample data\")\n41:             content = client.download_file(\"data.txt\")\n42:         \n43:         # Explicit session ID\n44:         client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n45:             session_id=\"pre-existing-session\",\n46:             router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n47:         )\n48:         try:\n49:             result = client.execute(\"x = 1 + 1\")\n50:         finally:\n51:             client.close()\n52:     \"\"\"\n53:     \n54:     def __init__(\n55:         self,\n56:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n57:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n58:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n59:         verbose: bool = False,\n60:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n61:         timeout: float = 120.0,\n62:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n63:         token_path: Optional[str] = None,\n64:     ) -> None:\n65:         \"\"\"Initialize CodeInterpreterClient.\n66:         \n67:         Args:\n68:             namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n69:             router_url: Router base URL. Resolves from arg or ROUTER_URL env var\n70:             workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL. Resolves from arg or\n71:                                  WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var\n72:             verbose: Enable debug logging (default: False)\n73:             session_id: Existing session ID. If None, creates new session\n74:             timeout: Default request timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n75:             connect_timeout: Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n76:             token_path: Path to Kubernetes SA token file\n77:         \n78:         Raises:\n79:             ValueError: If required URLs not provided and env vars not set\n80:         \"\"\"\n81:         self.namespace = namespace\n82:         self.timeout = timeout\n83:         self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n84:         self.verbose = verbose\n85:         \n86:         log_level = \"DEBUG\" if verbose else \"INFO\"\n87:         self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=log_level)\n88:         \n89:         self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n90:         if not self.router_url:\n91:             raise ValueError(\n92:                 \"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL environment variable must be set\"\n93:             )\n94:         \n95:         self.workload_manager_url = workload_manager_url or os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")\n96:         if not self.workload_manager_url:\n97:             raise ValueError(\n98:                 \"workload_manager_url must be provided or \"\n99:                 \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable must be set\"\n100:             )\n101:         \n102:         self.session_id = session_id\n103:         \n104:         self.cp_client = ControlPlaneClient(\n105:             workload_manager_url=self.workload_manager_url,\n106:             namespace=self.namespace,\n107:             timeout=self.timeout,\n108:             connect_timeout=self.connect_timeout,\n109:             token_path=token_path,\n110:         )\n111:         \n112:         self.dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n113:             router_url=self.router_url,\n114:             namespace=self.namespace,\n115:             timeout=self.timeout,\n116:             connect_timeout=self.connect_timeout,\n117:         )\n118:         \n119:         if not self.session_id:\n120:             self.session_id = self.cp_client.create_session()\n121:             self.logger.debug(f\"Created new session: {self.session_id}\")\n122:         else:\n123:             self.logger.debug(f\"Using provided session_id: {self.session_id}\")\n124:     \n125:     def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\":\n126:         \"\"\"Context manager entry.\n127:         \n128:         Returns:\n129:             self: The current CodeInterpreterClient instance\n130:         \"\"\"\n131:         return self\n132:     \n133:     def __exit__(self, exc_type: Any, exc_val: Any, exc_tb: Any) -> None:\n134:         \"\"\"Context manager exit - ensures cleanup.\n135:         \n136:         Args:\n137:             exc_type: Exception type if an exception was raised\n138:             exc_val: Exception value if an exception was raised\n139:             exc_tb: Exception traceback if an exception was raised\n140:         \"\"\"\n141:         self.close()\n142:     \n143:     def execute(\n144:         self,\n145:         code: str,\n146:         language: str = \"python\",\n147:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n148:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n149:         \"\"\"Execute code in the code interpreter.\n150:         \n151:         Args:\n152:             code: Code to execute\n153:             language: Programming language (default: \"python\")\n154:             timeout: Optional per-call timeout override in seconds\n155:         \n156:         Returns:\n157:             Parsed JSON response from the code interpreter\n158:         \n159:         Raises:\n160:             ValueError: If session_id is not initialized\n161:             CommandExecutionError: If code execution returns non-zero exit code\n162:         \n163:         Example:\n164:             result = client.execute(\"x = 1 + 1; print(x)\")\n165:             print(result[\"output\"])\n166:         \"\"\"\n167:         if not self.session_id:\n168:             raise ValueError(\"CodeInterpreter session_id is not initialized\")\n169:         \n170:         self.logger.debug(f\"Executing code: {code[:100]}...\")\n171:         \n172:         response = self.dp_client.execute(\n173:             session_id=self.session_id,\n174:             code=code,\n175:             language=language,\n176:             timeout=timeout,\n177:         )\n178:         \n179:         result = response.json()\n180:         \n181:         if result.get(\"exit_code\", 0) != 0:\n182:             raise CommandExecutionError(\n183:                 command=code,\n184:                 exit_code=result.get(\"exit_code\", 0),\n185:                 output=result.get(\"output\", \"\"),\n186:             )\n187:         \n188:         return result\n189:     \n190:     def upload_file(\n191:         self,\n192:         file_path: str,\n193:         file_content: bytes,\n194:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n195:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n196:         \"\"\"Upload a file to the code interpreter session.\n197:         \n198:         Args:\n199:             file_path: Path/filename for the uploaded file\n200:             file_content: File content as bytes\n201:             timeout: Optional per-call timeout override in seconds\n202:         \n203:         Returns:\n204:             Parsed JSON response from the upload operation\n205:         \n206:         Raises:\n207:             ValueError: If session_id is not initialized\n208:         \"\"\"\n209:         if not self.session_id:\n210:             raise ValueError(\"CodeInterpreter session_id is not initialized\")\n211:         \n212:         self.logger.debug(f\"Uploading file: {file_path}\")\n213:         \n214:         response = self.dp_client.upload_file(\n215:             session_id=self.session_id,\n216:             file_path=file_path,\n217:             file_content=file_content,\n218:             timeout=timeout,\n219:         )\n220:         \n221:         return response.json()\n222:     \n223:     def download_file(\n224:         self,\n225:         file_path: str,\n226:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n227:     ) -> bytes:\n228:         \"\"\"Download a file from the code interpreter session.\n229:         \n230:         Args:\n231:             file_path: Path/filename of the file to download\n232:             timeout: Optional per-call timeout override in seconds\n233:         \n234:         Returns:\n235:             File content as bytes\n236:         \n237:         Raises:\n238:             ValueError: If session_id is not initialized\n239:         \"\"\"\n240:         if not self.session_id:\n241:             raise ValueError(\"CodeInterpreter session_id is not initialized\")\n242:         \n243:         self.logger.debug(f\"Downloading file: {file_path}\")\n244:         \n245:         response = self.dp_client.download_file(\n246:             session_id=self.session_id,\n247:             file_path=file_path,\n248:             timeout=timeout,\n249:         )\n250:         \n251:         return response.content\n252:     \n253:     def close(self) -> None:\n254:         \"\"\"Close the client and release resources.\n255:         \n256:         This method closes both control plane and data plane HTTP sessions.\n257:         It also deletes the session if it was created by this client.\n258:         \"\"\"\n259:         self.logger.debug(\"Closing CodeInterpreterClient\")\n260:         \n261:         if self.dp_client:\n262:             self.dp_client.close()\n263:         \n264:         if self.cp_client:\n265:             if self.session_id:\n266:                 self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n267:             self.cp_client.close()\n268:         \n269:         self.logger.debug(\"CodeInterpreterClient closed\")\n\n(End of file - total 269 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Code Interpreter Client for the agentcube SDK.\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nimport os\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom .clients.code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\nfrom .clients.control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\nfrom .exceptions import CommandExecutionError\nfrom .utils.log import get_logger\n\n\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for Code Interpreter operations.\n    \n    This client manages session lifecycle and provides a simplified\n    interface for code execution and file operations.\n    \n    Attributes:\n        namespace: Kubernetes namespace","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py","time":{"start":1775885866691,"end":1775885866708}}}}
