{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886158449,"sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0f33fb001P8rQTe6akEouK1","messageID":"msg_d7b0f15d8001m6Gv1l0Qz0HC5k","sessionID":"ses_284f48b9fffeAzMtlRGIfh6tQM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_eddeddb291364c2881e813e3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Dify Plugin\n\nAgentCube Code Interpreter integration for the Dify AI platform. Execute Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript code in secure Kubernetes sandboxes directly from your Dify applications.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Secure Code Execution**: Run code in isolated Kubernetes sandbox environments\n- **Multiple Languages**: Support for Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript\n- **Session Management**: Reuse sessions for stateful interactions\n- **File Operations**: Upload and download files to/from the sandbox\n- **Command Execution**: Execute shell commands in addition to code\n\n## Installation\n\n1. Install the plugin dependencies:\n   ```bash\n   pip install -r requirements.txt\n   ```\n\n2. Configure the plugin in your Dify instance by uploading the plugin package.\n\n## Usage\n\n### Basic Code Execution\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n) as client:\n    result = client.execute(\"print('Hello, World!')\")\n    print(result[\"output\"])\n```\n\n### Session Reuse\n\n```python\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n    session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n)\ntry:\n    result = client.execute(\"x = 1 + 1\")\n    result2 = client.execute(\"print(x)\")  # x is still defined\nfinally:\n    client.close()\n```\n\n### File Operations\n\n```python\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n) as client:\n    # Upload a file\n    client.upload_file(\"data.txt\", b\"sample data\")\n    \n    # Download a file\n    content = client.download_file(\"data.txt\")\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe plugin requires the following configuration in Dify:\n\n- **Router URL**: Base URL of the AgentCube router service\n- **Workload Manager URL**: Base URL of the AgentCube workload manager service\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Python 3.12 or later\n- Dify platform with plugin support\n- Access to AgentCube services (router and workload manager)\n- Kubernetes cluster with AgentCube deployed\n\n## License\n\nApache 2.0\n\n## Support\n\nFor issues and feature requests, please open an issue on the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube).\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/dify-plugin/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/dify-plugin/main.py\">\nERROR [3:6] Import \"dify_plugin\" could not be resolved\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py\">\nERROR [5:6] Import \"dify_plugin\" could not be resolved\nERROR [6:6] Import \"dify_plugin.errors.tool\" could not be resolved\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\">\nERROR [6:6] Import \"dify_plugin\" could not be resolved\nERROR [7:6] Import \"dify_plugin.entities.tool\" could not be resolved\nERROR [8:6] Import \"agentcube\" could not be resolved\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detec